<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="656" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Calderon</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peruvian Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington,
                                        D. C.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-05-09"><hi rend="italic">May 9,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 14.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to express to your
                            excellency, in the name of my Government, the gratefulness of the
                            Peruvian people and Government <pb facs="0782" n="694" xml:id="pg_694"/>
                            for the message of sympathy delivered by Minister Irving Dudley, in the
                            name of the American people and of His Excellency President Roosevelt,
                            on the occasion of the sorrowful bereavement suffered by Peru.</p>
                        <p>Adding my own thanks, it affords me pleasure to renew, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Manuel Alvarez
                            Calderon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>